body_content.explanation: not easily influenced or affected by something:
examples: These tiny creatures seem to be insusceptible to antibiotics.
Even the boring world of accountancy is not insusceptible to a little glamour from time to time.

body_content.explanation: If an idea or statement is insusceptible, it is not able to be understood, proved, explained, etc. in a particular way:
examples: The decision is insusceptible of judicial review.
It was just a stream of incoherent images that was wholly insusceptible of rational interpretation.
